Jun 9, 2014 ... As Mark Twain execrates Fenimore Cooper he does something else: he spells 
out what he feels are the hallmarks of good writing. ... author claims that they are; 
its humor is pathetic; its pathos is funny; its conversations are -- oh! indescribable; 
its love-scenes odious; its English a crime against the language.
